st to have the chair return the meeting to the regular order of business.";i:50;s:94:"This motion may be made only when there is no other privileged motion on the floor but may be.";i:51;s:18:"Apr 28 17 at 1931.";i:52;s:241:"The question is whether routinely using both words -- chairman for men and chairperson for women -- is linguistically appropriate since the gender neutral chairperson has acquired female gender connotation at least in India as a consequence.";i:53;s:18:"Apr 28 17 at 1935.";i:54;s:144:"Once the quorum is established the board chair should offer thanks to any board directors who made special contributions since the last meeting.";i:55;s:92:"The board chair should give a short speech about the boards role in adhering to the mission.";i:56;s:89:"The talk may also include an anecdote about someone who benefitted from the organization.";}}